  <!-- METHODOLOGY -->
  <section class="methodology">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="frame">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow"><span class="num">No. 02</span><span class="rule-mini"></span>How we publish</div>
          <h2>Sourced, verified, on the <em>record.</em></h2>
        </div>
        <div class="body">
          <p>
            Every case study is co-authored with the member company at the center of it. <strong>Financial figures are pulled from the member&rsquo;s own ledger</strong> and reviewed by the firm&rsquo;s leadership before publication. We don&rsquo;t use composite communities, anonymised vendors, or estimates dressed up as outcomes.
          </p>
          <p>
            Member firms own the right to refuse publication of any number or detail at any stage. The case is shipped only when both the member and the cooperative are willing to put their names on it.
          </p>
          <div class="rules">
            <div class="rule">
              <span class="k">Rule 01</span>
              <span class="v">Numbers come from the member ledger.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="rule">
              <span class="k">Rule 02</span>
              <span class="v">The member firm has final approval.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="rule">
              <span class="k">Rule 03</span>
              <span class="v">No anonymised vendors or composite communities.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="rule">
              <span class="k">Rule 04</span>
              <span class="v">Outcomes are tracked at <span class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[12, 24, 36]</span> months.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
